Gold Mountain first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]] formed from parts of Iron Horse and Valley Ranch CDPs and additional area.<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Gold Mountain had a population of 73. The population density was {{convert|12.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Gold Mountain was 71 (97%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (1%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], and 1 (1.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 2 persons (3%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Gold Mountain CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0630339 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

There were 32 households, of which 22 were [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] and 2 were one person living alone.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gold Mountain CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0630339 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref> The median age was 61.9{{nbsp}}years.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 82 housing units at an average density of {{convert|13.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 32 (39%) were occupied. Of these, 23 (72%) were owner-occupied, and 9 (28%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

